üß† 1. Emotional Branding
‚Ä¢	Used by: Nike, Coca-Cola, Apple
‚Ä¢	Concept: Focuses on creating an emotional connection between the brand and the consumer (e.g., inspiration, belonging, happiness).
‚Ä¢	Example: Nike‚Äôs ‚ÄúJust Do It‚Äù isn‚Äôt about shoes ‚Äî it‚Äôs about motivation and pushing limits.

üåç 2. Lifestyle Marketing / Experience Marketing
‚Ä¢	Used by: Red Bull, Starbucks, GoPro
‚Ä¢	Concept: Sell the lifestyle or experience surrounding the product ‚Äî not just the product itself.
‚Ä¢	Example: Red Bull promotes extreme sports and adventure, not just an energy drink.

üì¢ 3. Influencer & Celebrity Marketing
‚Ä¢	Used by: Adidas, Pepsi, Calvin Klein
‚Ä¢	Concept: Leveraging trusted figures with large followings to promote products.
‚Ä¢	Example: Adidas collaborations with Kanye West (Yeezy) and Beyonc√© (Ivy Park).

üì¶ 4. Content Marketing
‚Ä¢	Used by: HubSpot, Apple, LEGO
