‚Ä¢	Example: LEGO‚Äôs YouTube channel and movies ‚Äî storytelling instead of just selling toys.

üìà 5. Product Placement
‚Ä¢	Used by: Coca-Cola, BMW, Ray-Ban
‚Ä¢	Concept: Integrating products into movies, shows, music videos, or games.
‚Ä¢	Example: Ray-Ban sunglasses in Top Gun skyrocketed their sales.

üß™ 6. FOMO & Scarcity Marketing
‚Ä¢	Used by: Supreme, Apple (product launches), Tesla (pre-orders)
‚Ä¢	Concept: Create urgency by limiting availability or offering exclusive drops.
‚Ä¢	Example: Supreme drops weekly limited items that sell out within minutes.

üîÅ 7. Loyalty and Rewards Programs
‚Ä¢	Used by: Starbucks, Amazon Prime, Sephora
‚Ä¢	Concept: Reward frequent buyers to keep them coming back.
‚Ä¢	Example: Starbucks Rewards encourages repeated purchases through stars and perks.

üí¨ 8. Word-of-Mouth / Referral Marketing
‚Ä¢	Used by: Dropbox, Tesla
‚Ä¢	Concept: Encourage users to share the product with others, sometimes with incentives.
‚Ä¢	Example: Dropbox‚Äôs early growth came from giving users free storage for referrals.

üîç 9. Search Engine & Performance Marketing
‚Ä¢	Used by: Amazon, Airbnb, every major e-commerce brand
